    <briefdescription>
<para>PWM event callback structure. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Used to register an event callback in the driver instance callback list. As many callbacks as needed can be added as long as each of them are unique pointers of struct <ref refid="structpwm__event__callback" kindref="compound">pwm_event_callback</ref>. Beware such structure should not be allocated on stack.</para>
<para>Note: to help setting it, see <ref refid="group__pwm__interface_1gaf87ef431d50a482910e77e49d52a2e13" kindref="member">pwm_init_event_callback()</ref>. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
